defaultCardiff University is among the top tier of Britain’s research intensive universities and is a member of the Russell Group of Univers
defaultities. The University has 17 STEM Schools 
default(including the School of Medicine) 
defaultwithin two of its three Colleges
default: the College of 
defaultBiomedical and Life Sciences and
default the College of 
defaultPhysical Sciences
default and Engineering
default.
default Of its 27,744 students, 14,754 are in 
defaultSTEM
default (58.3% female, 41.7%male).
default 
defaultThe number of academic staff in STEMM schools are 2065 of which1230 Males (59.5%) and 835 females (40.5%)
defaultThe University is committed to addressing the historic under-representation of women across the sector at all levels of aca
defaultdemic employment, and believes that the best way of undertaking this is through embedding equality and diversity into the University culture.
default The university has a structure 
defaultthat 
defaultaims to 
defaulttackle stereotyping and gender bias and provide ways to embed equality
default into everyday activities.
default It starts with the Vice Chancellor and the Deputy Vice-Chancellor leading on equality and diversity and implementing a strategic equality plan which includes mandatory equality and diversity training.
