default(b)
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultWhen women leave academia, what careers do they transition into? What are the consequences of scientifically trained women applying their skills in different employment sectors?
default&#xa0;
default8
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultResearch tends to show that some women who leave academia 
defaultdue to 
defaultfamily commitments have periods at home before attempting to move into other careers. Both these and others who leave academia for other reasons may move into administrative roles within a higher education institution
default, into science teaching at secondary or
default further education level
default or into roles in business and commerce. In 
defaultall
default cases they are likely to put their scientific training to positive effect by 
defaultusing 
defaulttheir 
defaultscientific knowledge, 
defaultand
default their 
defaultability to view problems 
defaultin general 
defaultfrom an objective, ‘scienti
defaultfic’ point of view
default.
default9
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultThis means that scientifically trained women who leave academia are 
defaultunlikely to be
default lost to
default productive employment and indeed are likely to make important contributions to the educational, social
default,
default business
default and economic
default good of the country
default. However, given the relatively 
defaultlow
default number of women in academic science employment, it is the case that this 
defaultunder-
defaultrepresentation is exacerbated by every woman who takes the decision to leave scientific academia.
default It also means that the unique contributions
default and perspectives these women could bring to academic science 
defaultare
default lost
default, at the same time representing a missed opportunity to encourage and stimulate the
default scientific aspirations o
defaultf other
default young 
defaultwomen.
