defaultUniversitie
defaults
default should promote the academic career
default and the many benefits associated with it, such as the flexible working arrangements / generous annual leave entitlement,
default at events to its own undergraduates and PhD students.  
default14
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultUniversity appointment committees could lo
defaultok for a new way in measuring the output of an individual, such as normalising by the number of years working in the post, which takes into consideration part-time work and maternity leave. 
default This is currently used in evaluating research output in the Rese
defaultarch Excellence Framework (REF)
default.
default15
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultAs mentioned earlier, women in academia can be 
defaultdisproportionately
default penalised by ‘out-of hours’ working patterns, since they are more likely than men to have caring commitments.
default For this reason, it behoves institutions to take into account the need that women scientists may have to keep ‘regular’ hours and to accommodate work arrangements that allow this. Nor should such accommodation be seen as women receiving particular privile
defaultges but rather as a necessary quid pro quo for the diversity of talents
default,
default approaches 
defaultand 
defaultinnovation
default 
defaultthat a diverse workforce necessarily brings to a discipline and 
defaultto 
defaultan institution. 
default16
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultUniversities should seek to give special prominence to women who have gai
defaultned positions of leadership and academic authority in the institution in order to provide role models for other aspiring female academics. 
default17
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultOn a practical level, universities should make sure that events essential for normal participation in academic life 
default(meetings, outside lectures, etc.) are held at times of day that are not likely to disadvantage female scientists with family commitments.  
