defaultWhat role should the Government have in encouraging the 
defaultretention of women in academic STEM careers?
default&#xa0;
default19
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultCan the government find a way of mitigating the precarious material situation that many postdoctoral and early career science researchers find themselves in? If a central fund were available to offer more secur
defaulte, or longer-term, employment to these staff it would benefit both men and women. But, crucially, it would almost certainly mean that proportionately a larger percentage of female than male staff would feel sufficiently comfortable not to contemplate the p
defaultossibility of leaving academic research. This would especially be the case for female staff with family commitments on whom pressure
defaults
default can already be great without the added stress of not being sure if contract renewal is likely in the near future.
